Articles.Content: I didn't see any mention either way in the OP, but is this compatible with rescale? I'd like to make a 2.5x rescale so BDB is properly balanced.

3 hours ago, birdog357 said:

I didn't see any mention either way in the OP, but is this compatible with rescale? I'd like to make a 2.5x rescale so BDB is properly balanced.

I'd be interested to know as well - every time I've tried it it's hung on loading. I do have about a million others mods though, and I haven't had time to try and properly isolate the cause of the problem.
I had tried to add this planet pack to an existing modded install with rescale and it hung at loading. I built a new install with the same mods minus rescale and it works so it may not be compatible?

15 hours ago, birdog357 said:

I had tried to add this planet pack to an existing modded install with rescale and it hung at loading. I built a new install with the same mods minus rescale and it works so it may not be compatible?

Ah... that doesn't sound good for compatibility. I'm going to do some more testing when I'm home from work.

Edit: I've narrowed down the problem to Sigma Dimensions and Alternis Kerbol. I made a fresh install and loaded Sigma Dimensions on its own; it worked perfectly. Same with the Outer Planets Mod added. Then I added Alternis Kerbol and it started hanging again. Guess this means they aren't compatible. I have the logs file if anyone wants to take a look at it - I would but I'd have no idea how to read any of it.

Edited October 8, 2019 by DelicousPi
Update from earlier

I just did a clean install with the minimum mods to load this planet pack and it worked, then I added SD and rescale. Got a crap ton of MM errors and it failed to load. Looks like an easy rescale ain't gonna happen.
